<item>
            <title>[HIVE-5812] HiveServer2 SSL connection transport binds to loopback address by default</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-5812</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The secure socket transport implemented as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-5351&quot; title=&quot;Secure-Socket-Layer (SSL) support for HiveServer2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-5351&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-5351&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, binds to loopback address by default. If the bind interface gets used only if its explicitly defined in the hive-site or via environment.&lt;br/&gt;
This behavior should be same as non-SSL transport.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
